 comments : 
 ---------
	Comments are written just for user understanding purpose.
        Comments maintains the good documentability.
	These statements are not a part of code.

	These statements are removed during compilation process and creates excutable file.           	

	Comments are 2 types.
	1) Single line comments (//----------)
	2) multiple line comments (/* -------
				      -------
				      -------
				      ------- */)


  pre-processor directives:
  -------------------------
	The statements starts with '#' symbol is called pre-processor directives.

 	There are some of the pre-processor directives are
 frequently used. They are

	1) #include  2) #define  3) #if  4) #else 5) #ifdef
	6) #ifndef   7) #elif  8)#endif  9) #undef 10) #pragma 
	and etc.

  In these very frequently used pre-processor directives are
  1) #include   2) #define 


 1) #include : This pre-processor directive is used for inclusion
    --------   of header files. 

    Header file : it is a file, which is extended with .h extension
    ------------  and it containes all the pre-defined function 
		  declarations and pre-defined macro definitions.  


	pre-defined function declarations
			+
